utterances.speaker: JOE BIDEN, PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
utterances.sentences: Now we look at 2022. I want to tell my Republican friends get ready, pal, you are going in for a problem. We have to keep making the case and if we do, I believe we are going to win. Let me say this again for the present. We are going to win in 2022. As Democrats, we know what we're for. What Republicans don't seem to be for anything. Name me something they are for. They're against everything. I don't know a single solitary world leader who wouldn't trade the problems of the president of the United States has for their problems. I don't know a single one.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: They are blocking every effort to provide --

utterances.speaker: REP. NANCY PELOSI (D), UNITED STATES SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE
utterances.sentences: It is an honor and pleasure to be here at this time of challenge and with the coronavirus, the national insecurity for families, national disaster, our country could not be more -- could not be better served than with these most experienced capable hands than your President Biden.

utterances.speaker: PELOSI
utterances.sentences: He is just perfect. The timing couldn't be better. I'm Madam, Vice President, we're inspired by your work for the people as you continue to be an invaluable partner to President Biden.

utterances.speaker: JESSE WATTERS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: -- because they have to.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But do you get the sense that they believe it?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: No, when the donors are there, you have to say we are going to win.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Especially if you have all these Democrats, what are you going to say, you know what? I'm unpopular, there's crime high, COVID cases, you guys are on your own this year. I'll pass the eggnog. Right. Like, that's not going to fly.

utterances.speaker: GERALDO RIVERA, FOX NEWS CORRESPONDENT-AT-LARGE
utterances.sentences: Deep on the police (Inaudible).

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right. It's like -- it's like a pep rally. Like, even if like the team is down, four touchdowns in the fourth quarter, like, there are still got to be pompoms, you have to root for the team. I understand that. But you can't blame Republicans, it's Sinema, it's Mansion, the squad, you know, it's the blue dogs, they're kind of slowing down his agenda. Why would the Republican Party strap their lassos to this train wreck? Look at this guy. He is unpopular. His policies are making everything worse. If he was popular and he was doing good things, you would probably have maybe 10 to 15 Senate Democrats joining that agenda. But you are not going to see that and that's clear. Nancy Pelosi, Mr. Perfect. I am old enough to remember when a couple Republicans were a little praise worthy of Donald Trump at a cabinet meeting and it was like the media framed it as a bunch of suck-ups to a dictator. Remember that whole thing? Mr. Perfect of all people?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I mean, that's you.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I mean, right.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I mean, you don't use that word lightly but only in politics do politicians just like go around and just kiss each other's butts. It's like, would we do that at this table? You are perfect --

utterances.speaker: BRIAN KILMEADE, FOX NEWS CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Brian Kilmeade.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Sarcastically.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: It is honor. Only sarcastically.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: You know, we are the king of sarcasm --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: -- when it comes to compliments. I would -- I'm sorry. Do you want to --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Go ahead, yes.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Sure. I forgot how to --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You met.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: I don't want to get in the post-game meeting with --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: You've been at --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Thank you. A couple of things. This is, if they called Donald Trump, perfect. We would have laughed out -- I mean, at this table because no one is perfect except you. But I want to just answer a question what are Republicans for? And I'm not in charge of the agenda but just by listening to the interviews and talking to some of them they like to drill. They would like to get the energy costs down so they can do that by getting LNG. They would stop the Nord Stream 2 pipeline. They would have actually went out of the way to arm the Ukrainians and give them help and give them strategy and maybe put some advisers on the ground to let the Russians know what's going to happen. Also, they were going to investigate China and the origin of the COVID virus and they were going to finish the wall. After all we have the receipts, it was paid for. That's what they would be doing. So, it's not -- it's not what they are for. Therefore, these things that's just off the top of my head.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: That's good for to have off the top of your head.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Can I --

utterances.speaker: JEANINE PIRRO, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: It's very good.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: -- pause that question, though? So, one of the things is that they've started to do is that the Build Back Better bill has been languishing for a while. It's not going to pass before Christmas. And now you have many Democrats who were saying, you know what, we should really work on the voting rights piece of our agenda.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: So, they are shelving Build Back Better already so, to me, that means like the longer this sits out there, the longer he might look like a lame duck president before he even gets to his first state of the union address.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Well, he is like a lame duck president because even the New York Times is writing an article about who should run for president telling him not to run for president. Cori Bush one of the squad members or one of the radical congresswomen is saying we're losing in 2022 because of you, Joe Biden.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: And what we've got are all of these people who already know that Joe Biden can't be the leader, he can't carry the Democrats. He kept talking about, I kept saying to myself what is he saying, why is he saying he is going to win? What he was saying was we stand with the people. We've made historic progress.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: What does that mean?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: We're going to make sure -- that's exactly my point.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: He says things that mean nothing. And, yes, Republicans are for nothing. Well, we are for law and order to begin with. We are for the wall. We are for education. We are for people making a responsible salary. I mean, this guy is all for inflation. And the bottom line is yes, I've been in politics. I ran five times. You really try to, you know, puff things up a little. But those people that he was talking to, even they don't believe it.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: And Nancy Pelosi coming out and saying that she is inspired by Kamala Harris' work. That's a quote. What work? I think she is still in --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Does she have a microscope? A Hubble telescope to find the work?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I think she is still in Vietnam.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I mean, I don't know. Did she come back from Vietnam, Kamala Harris?

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: I'm not sure.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I mean, it's all nonsense. It's all smoking mirrors and they're losing. And the numbers prove it.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Geraldo, the generic ballot, the congressional ballot has Republicans at a historic high. Like we're not ever seeing numbers like this. So, if you are a Republican, you should run in Vermont. You never know. Republicans could win everywhere.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: But to me, I didn't take any of that rhetoric seriously. To me, it was all, you know, kind of flamboyant irony.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Really? We're taking it completely seriously.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: You know, we're so unpopular let's say we are popular, ha-ha, inside joke and then go on. But I will -- I don't know the mechanisms of the economy. I don't pretend to. I'm not a businessman. You know, but I am an investor and the stock market was up almost 400 points today. And it's a --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Because of you.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- historic highs because of the fed. So, if the fed bails out the Democrats maybe our presumption that they're going to be routed in November will be tested. As things stand, I don't understand how you could possibly be optimistic holding the hands that the Democrats are holding. Look what just happened we're going to talk later in the program about the mayor of San Francisco completely --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- walking away from her policies from a year ago and as if it never happened. I believe the Democrats will do that increasingly. That they'll -- they'll bail --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I think you're right.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- just --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Stop Cori Booker.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: This isn't working, let's move on.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Cori Bush still says defund the police. And believe me, every time she has a microphone, she says the same thing which Joe Biden passes out every time she says it.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: I was going to say --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: So, they are also saying things, Jesse, like, if you don't cancel student loan debt you will not get the Democrats to coem out to vote. So, the progressives are already saying you are not going to fire up the base.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Young people don't vote in midterms anyway, Dana. Am I rigth about that?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: You sure?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I'm right about that. So, I don't think they are going to turn out for Joe Biden. I don't think that's not going to like, drive them to the polls. So, they have to pay what they were paying a year ago, big deal.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: OK. Just to chime in. There were 35-year-olds who would be outraged if all of a sudden, the loan that they just finished paying off --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: -- was paid off by all these 23-year-olds get their loans paid off. There's a lot of people take great pride in paying off their debt.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: And you think you break that agreement. One thing I'd like to add. Out of everybody that could replace Joe Biden, the one guy that I think could --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Gavin Newsom?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I predicted that. That was my prediction from the last show.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: OK. I don't agree with you, Joe Manchin.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Get out.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: But you can't get the progressive --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Joe Manchin.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Joe Manchin is more --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But you know what?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: We like him.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I'm going to give you my answer --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: We like him but we'll have our own candidate, a Republican candidate.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: He can't get enough from the right or the left to win.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: So, you disagree.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I'm going to give you my answer tonight --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes, I do.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: -- on Tucker on the a-block. So, I think --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Who do you think?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: That's a deep tease. I'll be on Tucker I'll be talking about this very --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: That is so deep, it's two shows away. That is

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: -- issue in the air on --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: That is --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Coming up next, what happened to blaming everything on the pandemic. Who the White House says is at fault for surging prices?

utterances.speaker: JEN PSAKI, WHITE HOUSE PRESS SECRETARY
utterances.sentences: The president, secretary of agriculture have both spoken to what we've seen as the greed of meat conglomerates. That is an area where people go to the grocery store and they're trying to buy a pound of meat, two pounds of meat, 10 pounds of meat. It is, the prices are higher. That is in his view and the view of our secretary of agriculture because of you could call it corporate greed, sure.

utterances.speaker: SEN. TOM COTTON (R-AK)
utterances.sentences: They are blaming everyone for this record inflation when it just goes back to Democratic policies. Look, we have had this pandemic for two years. First it was oil and gas companies. Now it's meat conglomerate. Maybe next week it's going to be the elf on the shelf when there aren't enough Christmas presents under the tree.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I always portray the rival as someone soft on crime. But you know, what really wasn't about them.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Bad at meat.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: No. It really was about --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Light on meat.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: It was about how strong I was. My record. What I did. I didn't really spend a lot of time trashing.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: And yet, politics aren't that now, it's that emphasizing all the - -

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Totally different.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- things. It seems to be emphasizing the negative.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: But can I talk about this?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Go ahead.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: I was like, (Inaudible)Jeanine's career. Noted in the segment.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: But here's the bottom line. They are always looking for an excuse.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: He doesn't want to admit that it's him. That it's his policy.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: That's politics.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: That's it's in -- that it's what?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: That's politics.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: That's not politics.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: He always blame the other guy.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: That is true. No, no, no. We got $3,500 that the average American family has to pay this year just to survive compared to last year. Last year was a really bad year, you know. The pandemic and everything else hit. But with Joe Biden in there he put money into the stimulus, into the infrastructure, this, and that, and the other thing his so-called Biden bipartisan infrastructure. And the bottom line is that with inflation that's the highest it's been in 40 years and we're at, what is it, 6.9 percent. You know? And he keeps wanting to pour more money in and that means your money is worth less because there is a lot more of it.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: But I want to stick with political stereotyping, Dana, and the Reagan administration. Remember welfare queens? He portrayed a whole class of people who became the enemy of the Republican voters in a very succinct way by focusing on one purported wealthy queen and they did the story didn't even pan out. But it was very effective politically. That's what you do to your rival. Don't you define your rival in this case big meat. Big meat is something people can remember.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But they are making up a rival. Right? So, like big meat is not their rival. Right? The big -- the rival is their -- are the Republicans, but it's also the fact that they have 69 percent of people in the ABC poll saying that they are disapprove of the way the Biden administration is handling inflation. That's a huge wake-up call. Where else can you get 69 percent of Americans to agree on today? They agree on that. So, what happens? So, a progressive group puts out poll tested messaging and says here's what you do to fight back. You just blame all of the private sector for being greedy. And they tried it with the energy companies. Now they are trying it with meat. Now I'm not saying that there isn't a problem especially when it comes to the producers, like the cattle ranchers. That is a problem, I do think, and that's one of the things that both the Trump administration and the Biden administration are looking into. But when it comes to consumer prices, all these other things fall into it. You have got to get the cows to market. You've got to get the trucks fueled. All of that stuff adds up. Packaging is more expensive. The supply chain.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: All of that happens. But if you ever wondered how the Democrats all get on -- get on one -- on the same page and they are all singing from the same song sheet, it's because you have a poll tested thing that goes out greed. That's it, let's talk about greed.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: So, every morning, today's headline was big meat?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: My last thing is that the problem is initially they said inflation wasn't happening. Then they said it's transitory/temporary. Then they're saying, well, it's going to get better right after the first of the year. Now they are saying actually it's the greedy meat packers.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Yes. It's so funny how the issue has to hit exactly right for it to the economy so we have to be the economy at that moment.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: I mean, for it to be the pandemic, whatever. It has to be -- and it just seems it's such a roll of the dice till the day of the election. Do politicians ever take responsibility?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: No. If you're good on --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Guy like you, you take responsibility.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I did.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You did you but you were a judge, judge.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: No, I was a D.A.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And if you are a politician --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I was a D.A., too.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: OK, true. But you know what, you are perfect. As Nancy Pelosi would say.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes, that makes three perfects at this table.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Is that better -- the perfect couple. So --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Not a couple.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: OK. Dana said something and she is right. The guy at the supermarket, Geraldo, with the little gun, the price gun it shoots it on the meat here, he gets a note from big meat every week what the price of the steaks is going to be. Where do you think that price comes from? You got increased transportation costs, labor costs.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Packaging costs, fuel costs, energy costs. It's all expensive. So, big meat is carrying a lot of costs so they are going to raise prices. You don't get to become big meat by selling meat for free, Geraldo.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: I get that. I get that.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: If you sell meat for free you become little meat. And you don't want to be little meat.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Do you have that graph, that funky graph on how the price of gas has really plummeted. Biden --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: What? Ten cents?

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Look at that. That looks very dramatic.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Geraldo, that's not dramatic. That's 10 cents.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: No. But that's -- wait a second.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: That's 10 cents.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I will --

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: I'm the (Inaudible) of the segment.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: OK.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Put the graph back, please. It looks like there's been a dramatic drop in the price of gasoline.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: But as my young colleague points out, that's only 10 cents. They've squashed the vertical --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- to make that graph looked like the price of gas --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: They keep doing this. It's embarrassing.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: -- is plummeting.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes. It's a slick sales job.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Now did you learn a little something?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I already knew it but now the audience knows how slick the Democrats are.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: It went down 10 cents in two weeks, Geraldo, is that because big oil is less greedy? No, because Omicron has all the oil traders bidding the price down.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: And by the way, with big meat I don't like the idea that John Dutton from Yellowstone is rising prices like that. It doesn't fit in my head.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: I have not seen Yellowstone. But I will say this.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: He do not say --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Meat is not even the biggest problem. It looks like t used cars is up 31 percent.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Gas is up 58 percent. Meat is at 13 percent.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Then you got furniture following right behind that, jewelry.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: They say that used --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: So, it affects everybody, and as you mentioned before $3,500 per family. I get it. So, what you'd do is, you don't have to have all the answers but you have to try. And the minute I think you just diminished your argument when you set up somebody as the fall guy. In this case it's corporations, big meat, the we have corporations' big oil. And you don't have to create an enemy. The other thing is and no offense but the press secretary should not be answering complex economic problems. Have the treasury secretary out there.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: No, that's a problem.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: The labor secretary out there.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: That's a --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Can I tell you something how that works?

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: This was you don't big meat statements that people mock for 24 hours. I'd like to have an expert that knows more than the reporters out and front.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes. Find out.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Let me tell you what happens. When the economy is good and you have good news, you can find anybody from the Treasury Department to (Inaudible) to the briefing.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: They don't want to go.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Soon as it stops, they are busy. They can't show up. Let me tell you something. It happened in the fall of 2008, and I was learning what a credit default swap was every single day.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: But I'm sure you're sitting to the press corps.

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Well, that's criminal.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
utterances.sentences: Didn't you at the story of the day was? I remember when Jimmy Carter was president and I was in Latin America covering his trip to South America. And somebody ran through the hallways at four in the morning, the story is Amy Carter. The story is Amy Carter. So, everybody wrote about Amy Carter that day. It says the press can be easily steered --

utterances.speaker: KILMEADE
utterances.sentences: Wow.

utterances.speaker: RIVERA
